SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 289.060 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 289.060 1. Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, a
3 law enforcement agency shall, not later than 48 hours before any
4 interrogation or hearing is held relating to an investigation
5 conducted pursuant to NRS 289.057, provide a written notice to the
6 peace officer who is the subject of the investigation. If the law
7 enforcement agency believes that any other peace officer has any
8 knowledge of any fact relating to the complaint or allegation against
9 the peace officer who is the subject of the investigation, the law
10 enforcement agency shall , not later than 48 hours before the peace
11 officer must appear and be interviewed in connection with the
12 investigation conducted pursuant to NRS 289.057, provide a
13 written notice to the peace officer advising the peace officer that he
14 or she must appear and be interviewed as a witness in connection
15 with the investigation. Any peace officer who serves as a witness
16 during an interview must be allowed a reasonable opportunity to
17 arrange for the presence and assistance of a representative
18 authorized by NRS 289.080. Any peace officer specified in this
19 subsection may waive the notice required pursuant to this section.
20 2. The notice provided to the peace officer who is the subject
21 of the investigation must include:
22 (a) A description of the nature of the investigation . [;]
23 (b) A summary of alleged misconduct of the peace officer [;]
24 setting forth with specificity the alleged acts or omissions
25 constituting the misconduct and the date, time and location of the
26 alleged misconduct. If the date, time or location of the alleged
27 misconduct is unknown, the summary must specify that the date,
28 time or location is unknown. If there are multiple allegations of
29 misconduct, the summary must describe each allegation of
30 misconduct.
31 (c) The date, time and place of the interrogation or hearing . [;]
32 (d) The name and rank of the officer in charge of the
33 investigation and the officers who will conduct any interrogation or
34 hearing . [;]
35 (e) The name of any other person who will be present at any
36 interrogation or hearing . [; and]
37 (f) A statement setting forth the provisions of subsection 1 of
38 NRS 289.080.
39 3. The law enforcement agency shall:
40 (a) Interview or interrogate the peace officer during the peace
41 officer’s regular working hours, if reasonably practicable, or revise
42 the peace officer’s work schedule to allow any time that is required
